    {
      "id": "b90bf133-dd2f-421e-9631-8495e6e541c8",
      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soient $a_1, \\dots, a_n \\in \\Z$ distincts.",
        "html": "<p>Soient <span class=\"math inline\">\\(a_1, \\dots, a_n \\in \\Z\\)</span> distincts.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "a02540ce-06a5-401d-a2f8-6c6eb96213f7",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que $(X-a_1) \\dots (X-a_n) - 1$ est irr{\\'e}ductible dans ${\\Z[X]}$.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\((X-a_1) \\dots (X-a_n) - 1\\)</span> est irr<span>é</span>ductible dans <span class=\"math inline\">\\({\\Z[X]}\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "ac7588e9-8b52-4015-a464-bb33dcaa3cab",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Si $P = QR$ alors $Q(a_i)R(a_i) = -1  \\Rightarrow  Q(a_i) = -R(a_i) = \\pm1$,\n    donc $Q+R$ a $n$ racines, donc est nul, et $P = -Q^2$~:\n    contradiction pour $x \\to \\infty$.",
        "html": "<p>Si <span class=\"math inline\">\\(P = QR\\)</span> alors <span class=\"math inline\">\\(Q(a_i)R(a_i) = -1  \\Rightarrow  Q(a_i) = -R(a_i) = \\pm1\\)</span>, donc <span class=\"math inline\">\\(Q+R\\)</span> a <span class=\"math inline\">\\(n\\)</span> racines, donc est nul, et <span class=\"math inline\">\\(P = -Q^2\\)</span> : contradiction pour <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x \\to \\infty\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "2081e364-8581-4f45-afdc-0343919a6641",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "M{\\^e}me question avec $(X-a_1) \\dots (X-a_n) + 1$, $n$ impair.",
        "html": "<p>M<span>ê</span>me question avec <span class=\"math inline\">\\((X-a_1) \\dots (X-a_n) + 1\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(n\\)</span> impair.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "6908c0e5-2353-4654-bb51-cb3bc09a3ca3",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "M{\\^e}me raisonnement : $P = Q^2$, donc\n    $Q^2-1 = (Q-1)(Q+1) = (X-a_1) \\dots (X-a_n)$.\n    \\par\n    On r{\\'e}partit les facteurs entre $Q-1$ et $Q+1$ : $n = 2p$, contradiction.",
        "html": "<p>M<span>ê</span>me raisonnement : <span class=\"math inline\">\\(P = Q^2\\)</span>, donc <span class=\"math inline\">\\(Q^2-1 = (Q-1)(Q+1) = (X-a_1) \\dots (X-a_n)\\)</span>.</p>\n<p>On r<span>é</span>partit les facteurs entre <span class=\"math inline\">\\(Q-1\\)</span> et <span class=\"math inline\">\\(Q+1\\)</span> : <span class=\"math inline\">\\(n = 2p\\)</span>, contradiction.</p>\n"
      }
    }
  ],
  "preview": "<p>Soient <span class=\"math inline\">\\(a_1, \\dots, a_n \\in \\Z\\)</span> distincts.</p>\n"
